    "body": "Book I does not begin at the beginning.\n\nIt begins where Book 0 leaves the witness: inside a file that should not exist, listening to a dead commander explain why every clean answer is a trap. The archive has opened beyond the public node. The sealed Act II gate is gone. The full directive is now readable.\n\nThe files ahead are not creator notes. They are not an outline. They are the recovered sequence: the dead unit, the machine, Veyr, Glass Psalm, and the final directive Rook left behind for whoever survived enough doubt to keep reading.\n\nProceed carefully. The archive is no longer asking whether you believe it. It is measuring what you do after belief becomes useless.",
